UglySTM32 is an environment for development STM32 microcontroller with CMSIS only. No HAL & LL.Just CMSIS & Makefile! A fork from https://github.com/STM32-base 
Just to make it simple, clean, & ugly :)

The structure :

UglySTM32
	|
	|base---|linker-----------|STM32F4xx -->STM32F4*.ld
	|	|make ------------|STM32F4xx -->common.mk			
	|	|startup ---------|STM32F4xx -->STM32F4*.s
	|
	|cmsis--|ARM-------|inc
	| 	|STM32F4xx-|inc--->STM32F4*.h
	|		   |src--->system_*.c 	
	|libraries
	|
	|projects|yourproject--|bin
	|		       |obj	
	|		       |src-->Makefile & main.c 	
	|			   
	|tools--|arm-none-eabi 
		|bin
		|lib
		|share

Download gcc-arm-none-eabi & extract at tools folder.
https://developer.arm.com/-/media/Files/downloads/gnu-rm/10.3-2021.10/gcc-arm-none-eabi-10.3-2021.10-x86_64-linux.tar.bz2

Just CD to your src project and type "make" to compile the source code & "make flash" to flashing stm32 chip.
